cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper deals with visual surveillance using UAVs and proposes a method for person ReID in aerial imagery. This is a core topic in computer vision and hence, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category.
2. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper discusses the use of UAVs for visual surveillance, which is a common application in robotics. Hence, cs.RO is also a likely sub-category.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed method for person ReID involves learning a discriminative and compact feature descriptor, which is a common task in AI. Hence, cs.AI is also a likely sub-category.
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The proposed method involves training a model in an end-to-end fashion, which is a common approach in machine learning. Hence, cs.LG is also a likely sub-category.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with visual data captured by UAVs, which can be considered as a form of multimedia. Hence, cs.MM is also a possible sub-category.
